HEADWORD: Clydesdale terrier
<hw>Clydesdale terrier</hw>. <def>One of a breed of small silky-haired
terriers related to, but smaller than, the Skye terrier, having smaller
and perfectly erect ears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

